      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### Elementwise functions\n"
      ],
      "id": "323c21cf"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "x = np.linspace(-1, 1, 11)\n",
        "x"
      ],
      "id": "5e8f7f84",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "y = np.sin(np.pi * x)"
      ],
      "id": "5f754d55",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "np.round(y, decimals=4)"
      ],
      "id": "45a6f8b4",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "np.add(np.sin(x)**2, np.cos(x)**2)"
      ],
      "id": "4f939324",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "np.sin(x)**2 + np.cos(x)**2"
      ],
      "id": "cee4d1ad",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "---\n"
      ],
      "id": "019d1166"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def heaviside(x):\n",
        "    return 1 if x > 0 else 0"
      ],
      "id": "bd852f73",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "heaviside(-1)"
      ],
      "id": "59915a07",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "heaviside(1.5)"
      ],
      "id": "36c64cdf",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "````\n",
        "```{{python}}\n",
        "x = np.linspace(-5, 5, 11)\n",
        "heaviside(x)\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "ValueError \n",
        "      1 x = np.linspace(-5, 5, 11)\n",
        "----> 2 heaviside(x)\n",
        "\n",
        "      1 def heaviside(x):\n",
        "----> 2     return 1 if x > 0 else 0\n",
        "\n",
        "ValueError: The truth value of an array with more than \n",
        "one element is ambiguous. Use a.any() or a.all()\n",
        "\n",
        "````\n"
      ],
      "id": "d00c27ac"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "heaviside = np.vectorize(heaviside)\n",
        "heaviside(x)"
      ],
      "id": "2bc1d3ba",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def heaviside(x):  # much better way\n",
        "    return 1 * (x > 0)\n",
        "\n",
        "heaviside(x)"
      ],
      "id": "ccc24b73",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
